cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the intersection of machine learning and social science, and how social theory can be used to address issues in this intersection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with social data. The paper also discusses issues of bias and fairness, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Finally, the paper touches on technical issues with data and models, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
